oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Postcard, "New type of Army Motor Kitchen."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A postcard bearing title "New type of Army Motor Kitchen." It is a color-tinted photograph of the army motor kitchen parked in a grassy field, with 3 soldiers working at the counter or waiting for service. The reverse is stamped with advertisement for Smiths Variety Store, Wayside, W. Va. Collected by Ethel Flesher Stewart of Parkersburg, W. Va.
